    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-03-21T04:10:39+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-21T04:10:39+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-20T17:40:39Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-20T17:40:39Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A ridge of high pressure will persist across the state. The high pressure centre associated with the ridge will become established in the Tasman Sea over the weekend. A trough moves over the south early next week with a cold front clipping the southeast mid week. A new ridge develops south of the Bight early to mid next week.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW010" description="West Coast" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-03-21T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-22T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-20T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-21T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. The chance of morning fog south of Streaky Bay. Light winds becoming south to southeasterly 15 to 25 km/h in the early afternoon. Daytime maximum temperatures in the mid to high 20s.</text>
                <text type="fire_danger">Moderate</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 10:10am to 5:10pm, UV Index predicted to reach 9 [Very High]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-03-22T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-23T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-21T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-22T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Sunny. The chance of morning fog south of Streaky Bay. Winds east to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h tending east to northeasterly in the early morning then tending east to southeasterly 15 to 25 km/h in the late afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 13 and 17 with daytime temperatures reaching the low 30s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-03-23T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-24T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-22T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-23T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. Slight chance of a shower south of Streaky Bay in the afternoon. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. Winds easterly 15 to 20 km/h tending north to northeasterly 15 to 25 km/h during the morning then tending east to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 17 and 20 with daytime temperatures reaching the low 30s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-03-24T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-25T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-23T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-24T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Sunny morning. The chance of a thunderstorm east of Ceduna in the afternoon and evening. Winds east to northeasterly 15 to 20 km/h tending north to northeasterly during the morning then shifting south to southeasterly during the afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 17 and 21 with daytime temperatures reaching the low to mid 30s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
